description: Nanny's Attic is the memories of an unwimpy grandmother - a feel good book with quick-read stories that picture the spirit of a child from newborn to age ninety-three. Many of the stories are hilarious, some poignant and some just a little wacky. All will bring back memories of your children, grandchildren and your own childhood. The book/journal format helps you to recapture and record your memorable kid moments in an attractive keepsake journal. Author's Bio: Carolyn Goddard is a grandmother of twenty years who enjoys travel, reading and anything that has to do with children of any age. Active in church and community affairs, she is a Rotary Paul Harris Fellow, sponsors children through Child Fund International and supports many child-related ministries. She loves her grandchildren unconditionally, but not blindly. "Never trust anyone under fifty." She lives in New Martinsville, West Virginia with her husband Fred, and freqently a house full of cheerleaders, athletes, adventurers and other teen-age malcontents. It should be noted that she is more than willing to blame misbehavior of any of the above on his side of the family. Carolyn views Nanny's Attic as an opportunity to use some humor and entertainment to bless more children. She will donate half of her net proceeds to organizations that help children.
title: Nanny's Attic - You're going to put that thermometer where?
